@{
    ViewBag.Title = "Benefits";
    Layout = "~/Views/Shared/_BasicLayout.cshtml";
}

<h1>Benefits</h1>

<h6>Combine & Version Assets</h6>
<p>Create a asset structure that fits your needs. Web Asset Bundler will take care of combining and versioning for you.</p>
<pre data-language="html">
@Html.Code(@"
//from many javascript or css assets
<link href=""/Content/jquery-ui.custom.css"" />
<link href=""/Content/reset.css"" />
<link href=""/Content/reset.css"" />
<link href=""/Content/layout.css"" />
<link href=""/Content/download.css"" />
<link href=""/Content/documentation.css"" />
<script type=""text/javascript"" src=""/Scripts/jquery.js""></script>
<script type=""text/javascript"" src=""/Scripts/jquery-ui.js""></script>

//to single asset bundles
<link type=""text/css"" href=""/wab.axd/css/8190e9a67c00175a53de58ffc50ddee1/StyleSheets"" rel=""stylesheet"">
<script type=""text/javascript"" src=""/wab.axd/css/8190e9a67c00175a53de58ffc50ddee1/Script""></script>
")
</pre>

<h6>Automatic Browser Caching and Encoding</h6>
<p>Bundles are cached for 1 year (configurable) and are automatically served encoded in GZip/Deflate. Any changes to the contents of the
    bundle will automatically break the browser cache, forcing the browser to re-download the bundle.
</p>
